  "prompt": "What is the best book on the meaning of life?",
  "response": "There's no universally agreed \"best\" book on the meaning of life, as perspectives vary widely. However, some highly regarded philosophical works exploring this question include:\n\n1. Viktor Frankl's \"Man's Search for Meaning\"\n- Explores finding purpose through suffering and personal experience\n\n2. Albert Camus' \"The Myth of Sisyphus\"\n- Existentialist perspective on creating meaning in an absurd world\n\n3. Jean-Paul Sartre's \"Existentialism is a Humanism\"\n- Discusses individual responsibility in creating life's meaning\n\n4. Marcus Aurelius' \"Meditations\"\n- Stoic philosophy on living a meaningful life\n\n5. S\u00f8ren Kierkegaard's \"Either/Or\"\n- Explores personal choice and individual meaning\n\n6. Bertrand Russell's \"The Conquest of Happiness\"\n- Practical approach to finding meaning and contentment\n\n7. The Dalai Lama's \"The Art of Happiness\"\n- Buddhist perspective on finding purpose and inner peace\n\nThe \"best\" book depends on individual philosophical leanings, cultural background, and personal beliefs. I recommend exploring multiple perspectives to develop your own understanding.",
